:INFO
The Martha Wells Novel That Gets Overlooked for the Wrong Reason
Everyone who reads speculative fiction knows the Murderbot Diaries. Far fewer \
know Witch King, a standalone fantasy published in 2023 about a demon named Kai \
who wakes up drowned at the bottom of a well and works backward to understand \
who put him there. Martha Wells writes with the same intelligence and wit that \
made Murderbot beloved, but Witch King has a scope and emotional depth that the \
shorter format of those books does not attempt. It deserves more readers than it has.

:NOTE
Wells writes secondary characters better than most authors write leads.

:QUOTE [subtitle:Martha Wells, quotetype:PLAIN]
He had been many things before they drowned him. Not all of them were good things.

:JOURNEY
Reading Witch King
Section
Enjoyment
- Opening chapters | 5 | Immediately compelling
- World building | 5 | Through action
- Kai as protagonist | 5 | Genuinely alien | Most alien feeling lead in recent fantasy
- The ending | 4 | Complete and open

:CHECKLIST
Why to Read Witch King if You Have Only Read Murderbot
[ ] It shows what Wells can do with a longer format and a secondary world setting
[ ] The moral complexity is deeper than the Murderbot novellas allow room for
[ ] Kai is a completely different kind of character and equally worth spending time with
[ ] It stands alone, no series commitment needed to get the full experience

